.TH ox-subscribe 1  "ox-subscribe " 
.SH NAME
ox\-subscribe \- Subscribe to the event stream for an active session
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBox\-subscribe\fR [\fB\-\-session\-id\fR] [\fB\-\-event\-type\fR] [\fB\-\-where\fR] [\fB\-\-replay\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] 
.SH DESCRIPTION
Subscribe to the event stream for an active session
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-session\-id\fR \fI<SESSION_ID>\fR
Session (run) ID to subscribe to. If omitted, subscribes to the most recent active session
.TP
\fB\-\-event\-type\fR \fI<TYPE>\fR
Filter to specific event types (repeatable). If omitted, all events are streamed. Valid types: run_started, job_queued, job_started, job_completed, job_failed, job_skipped, gate_reached, gate_approved, run_completed, run_failed
.TP
\fB\-\-where\fR \fI<KEY=VALUE>\fR
Filter events by tag values on the originating job (repeatable, KEY=VALUE format, AND logic)
.TP
\fB\-\-replay\fR
Replay all events from session start before streaming live events. Without this flag, only new events are shown
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help
